<TEXT>
a recent series of books and articles and a sharp 
political debate have bared some of the darkest and most sensitive 
moments of italys fascist past 
the treatment of jews the conduct of italys communist party 
and the plight of italian soldiers left to choose sides between the 
nazis and the allies all have come under scrutiny 
some of the issues are being used as fuel in current political 
maneuvering particularly in the struggle between the communists 
and the socialists for dominance of the italian left 
others have surfaced as italys jewish community prepares to 
mark the 50th anniversary of the racial laws enacted by benito 
mussolinis fascist dictatorship which foreshadowed deportations 
to nazi death camps 
the controversy involving the alleged complicity in war crimes 
of president kurt waldheim in neighboring austria brought a 
reminder that italian as well as nazi troops were occupying the 
balkans 
the probing has touched some raw nerves 
when renzo de felice a leading historian who wrote a highly 
respected biography of mussolini lectured at rome university he 
was heckled and harassed by leftist students 
de felice recently suggested antifascism was mainly serving the 
communist party and should be abandoned but other books praise 
italians who fought fascism 
we all looked at ourselves as antifascist and on the side of 
the allies says furio colombo the president of fiat usa and 
a columbia university lecturer who wrote the preface to the italian 
edition of american historian susan zuccottis book the italians 
and the holocaust 
the book published here in march by mondadori gives generally 
high marks to italians noting that italy shares with denmark the 
merit of the highest percentage of jews saved but it also makes 
the point that italians bear a share of guilt 
more than 8000 jews were deported and only about 900 of them 
survived 
it shouldnt be possible any longer to boast of the minimum 
number of italian jews put to death said colombo in his 
preface only one italian jew persecuted and there were 
thousands would already represent a crime serious enough to force 
a collective rethinking of the past 
any confusion about italians coming to terms with the past can 
perhaps be attributed in part to the shifting loyalties that 
evolved as italy became bogged down in world war ii leaving the 
country in a no mans land between winners and losers at the 
end 
mussolini came to power in 1922 launched an invasion of 
ethiopia in 1936 and took italy into world war ii on the side of 
nazi germany and japan 
he was ousted from power in rome in july 1943 after allied 
forces landed in sicily in september 1943 italy surrendered 
unconditionally to the allies 
in the meantime the germans helped mussolini escape from prison 
and established him in a puppet regime in the north italian 
partisans captured mussolini and his mistress clara petacci on 
april 27 1945 shot them and hung their bodies upside down at a 
gasoline station near milan 
one of the bitterest quarrels to emerge has pitted communist and 
socialist party officials over whether palmiro togliatti who led 
the communists from 1927 until his death in 1964 had abandoned the 
partys founder antonio gramsci to fascist prison 
the allegations center over whether togliatti from his exile in 
moscow had not tried to press the soviet union to negotiate the 
freedom of gramsci known more as a liberal thinker than the party 
boss 
togliatti was neither a saint nor a hero said former 
socialist premier bettino craxi drawing the rage of the communist 
leadership 
historian de felices point is that italy is illserved by a 
continued use of antifascism as a political reference point as if 
antifascist meant democratic 
i dont say you have to forget fascism de felice said in an 
interview with the associated press i say that today that the 
use of the label antifascism has allowed the communists to present 
themselves as the other parties it has given them a common 
heritage 
de felice also contends that the postwar laws forbidding 
reestablishment of the fascist party are anachronistic since 
there is a neofascist party the italian social movement which 
has consistently gathered around 6 percent of the vote 
the historian also told milans corriere della sera that the 
myth of fascism is over noting that mussolinis granddaughter 
a budding actress recently posed topless in an italian mens 
magazine 
others disagree that its time to move on 
colombo for example said that while he may agree with de 
felice intellectually some signal still has to be given about 
the evils of fascism 
the jewish community of about 40000 plans major commemorations 
this fall of the enactment of the racial laws that expelled jews 
from government positions and the military and put restrictions on 
their work schooling and possession of property 
its too soon to say let bygones be bygones said tullia 
zevi president of the union of italian jewish communities 
jewish leaders note that until 1938 the jewish community was 
fully integrated in italian society holding important posts in the 
military and government and even the fascist party 
another a point of controversy is whether pope pius xii did all 
he could to save the jews the zuccotti book praises the efforts of 
individual priests to protect italian jews 
the vatican which has repeatedly defended the efforts of the 
pope on april 13 ran excerpts in its daily newspaper from a new 
book by a german historian contesting allegations against pius xii 
the newspaper losservatore romano called it a vibrant and 
direct response to the denigrators of the pontiff 
</TEXT>
