the first round of the presidential election was a 
historic moment for two political parties the farright national 
front achieved unprecedented support and the communist party 
tumbled to an alltime low 
perhaps most important for the future of france was the 145 
percent won by jeanmarie le pen president of the national front 
the party has emerged as a significant new force in french 
