<TEXT>
the old issues were blurred with ambivalence for 
some of the 60s revolutionaries who grappled with their past 
during a reunion at columbia university 
the adrenaline surge they remembered from the former struggle 
has been tempered by wistfulness perhaps because the dream didnt 
last 
it didnt just die it was profoundly defeated said tom 
hurwitz a freelance cinematographer who thought a majoritys greed 
overcame a minoritys ideals 
you become an anachronism and a very bitter one if youre 
not careful said bettina berch who was among the hundreds of 
former protesters who last weekend marked the 20th anniversary of a 
weeklong student uprising that shut down the ivy league campus 
one of the things that makes me sad is that people who are 
younger than us picked up on the drugs and forgot most of the rest 
of what we were saying said ann hunter 40 drugs were our 
biggest mistake 
during panel discussions a party and an indoor picnic they 
recalled how about 1000 people mostly students barricaded 
themselves inside five buildings the week of april 23 1968 the 
protest drew international attention to the issues of racism the 
vietnam war and the status quo in general 
this has plunged some of us into a lot of memories that one 
still feels ambivalent about said berch 
after college berch clung to her antiestablishment leanings 
she said she was kicked out of academia in a tenure fight after 
seven years of teaching at barnard college and is now writing a 
book 
