in cashstarved panama horacio icaza 
has added one of mankinds oldest forms of trade to his business 
skills he barters 
icaza whose firm casa del medico is the nations largest 
medical equipment supplier recently worked out a deal with the 
governmentowned water and power companies 
he pooled some of his employees water and electric bills then 
told the utilities he would erase a similar amount from the debts 
they owed his firm for laboratory equipment 
they agreed and debts on both side of the ledger were wiped out 
without any money changing hands 
panama suffering from sweeping us economic sanctions and the 
nearly twomonth closure of its onceformidable banking center has 
now become a barter economy 
it stops people from starving to death but it doesnt get the 
economy moving said a western european diplomat who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
