and a twoweek general strike in march have virtually paralyzed 
the economy 
the us dollar the national currency has become scarce 
its place has been partially filled by checks issued in small 
amounts by the government to pay its employees and social security 
recipients 
with those checks panamanians can buy groceries at supermarkets 
or clothing at department stores they also can send the checks 
back to the government to pay taxes or utility fees they owe the 
staterun water electric and telephone companies 
the checks say businessmen have become a quasicurrency 
