minority groups may feel betrayed by the courts order calling for 
reexamination of the 1976 case 
in addition to the impact of todays decision on the faith of 
victims of racial discrimination in a stable construction of the 
civil rights laws the order must also have a detrimental and 
enduring impact on the publics perception of the court as an 
impartial adjudicator stevens said 
