<TEXT>
here at a glance are highlights of actions 
taken monday by the supreme court 
 
racial discrimination 
 
the court said it will consider overturning a key civil rights 
precedent allowing people to sue private citizens accused of racial 
discrimination four dissenting justices accused the court of 
undermining the trust minority groups have in it 
the court in an extraordinary move said it will use a north 
carolina case involving charges of onthejob racial harassment to 
consider throwing out a 12yearold decision 
the case is patterson vs mclean credit union 87107 
 
phone porn 
 
the court let stand a ban on sexually explicit telephone dialup 
message services in arizona 
the justices without comment refused to hear arguments that 
the ban violates freespeech rights it was the first dialaporn 
case with which the court was confronted 
the case is carlin communications vs mountain states telephone 
amp telegraph co 871479 
 
prison publications 
 
the court agreed to consider giving federal prison wardens more 
power to decide what publications inmates may read 
the court said it will review a ruling that limits the authority 
of officials to censor reading material behind prison bars 
the case is meese vs abbott 871344 
 
agnew 
 
the court turned away an appeal by former vice president spiro 
t agnew in a lawsuit alleging he was cheated out of more than 2 
million for arranging a deal between a defense contractor and the 
argentine government 
the justices without comment refused to order the setting 
aside of more than 340000 in a special fund agnew and another 
businessman would receive if they win the lawsuit 
the case is agnew vs alicanto 871464 
 
air space 
 
the court let stand a ruling that property owners rights are 
not violated when they are required to remove structures that could 
interfere with lowflying planes 
the court citing the lack of a substantial federal 
question rejected an appeal by a cheyenne wyo man fined 200 
a day for refusing to trim a 48foot cottonwood tree on his 
property 
the case is rogers vs cheyenne 871462 
 
sex bias 
 
the court turned away a case in which missouri officials were 
found guilty of sex discrimination by not hiring enough women as 
highway maintenance workers 
the court without comment rejected an appeal by state 
officials who said lower courts improperly weighed the evidence 
the justices also refused to hear an appeal by women who said 
remedies ordered by the lower courts were inadequate 
the cases are missouri highway commission vs catlett 871415 
and catlett vs missouri highway commission 871416 
 
religious rights 
 
the court turned down an appeal by native hawaiians who say 
plans for developing geothermal energy in a volcanic area will 
violate their religious rights 
the court without comment let stand a ruling that the proposed 
development will not interfere unlawfully with access to sacred 
land by worshippers of the goddess pele 
the case is dedman vs hawaii board of land and natural 
resources 87605 
</TEXT>
