approved on monday a slightly different senate version giving 
jurisdiction over international child abduction cases to both state 
and federal courts 
the measure is intended to remove difficult timeconsuming 
legal issues involved in returning children abducted to another 
country or helping foreign parents recover children wrongfully 
taken to the united states 
