<TEXT>
the nuclear regulatory commission needs to 
improve its investigative office to ensure that its work is done 
competently and professionally according to a congressional study 
released monday 
the important mission and critical safety role of the nrc 
require that it possess a firstrate investigative capability 
the general accounting office said in the study which was released 
by the nrc 
gao the investigative wing of congress said the study was 
based on the review of three investigations made within the nuclear 
agency gao said that in two cases the work done by the nrcs 
office and inspector and auditor was not thorough enough 
one case involved allegations by an nrc inspector that superiors 
had pressured him to change findings in 1986 about safety 
conditions at the comanche peak steam electric station in texas 
the other involved alleged improper discussions in 1986 between 
victor stello the nrcs executive director of operations and 
steve white head of the tennessee valley authoritys nrcregulated 
nuclear program 
gao said its review supported the findings of nrc investigators 
who said neither matter was improper but in both cases gao said 
nrc investigators had not interviewed individuals with key roles 
the third case looked into nrcs investigation of how a copy of 
an internal nrc document turned up in 1985 in the files of the 
louisiana power and light cos waterford iii plant along with a 
memo from lpls holding company saying the document had been 
received from sources inside the nrc 
gao said notations on the copy indicated it was duplicated from 
the file copy in the office of nrc commissioner thomas roberts who 
was in charge of investigating the alleged leak 
gao was critical of the very limited investigation made by 
roberts but gao said it was unable to determine how the copy 
reached the regulated utility 
a properly conducted investigation might have provided nrc 
with the identity of the leaker according to gao 
the case gao said demonstrated that a regulated utility 
secured unauthorized access to nrc documents the ability to obtain 
such materials could impact on the nrcs enforcement program 
licensing functions and regulatory procedures 
the nrc should assure that its investigators conduct their 
work in a competent manner using professional standards said 
gao adding that there is a lack of coordination between the nrcs 
office of investigations and office of inspector and auditor 
nrc chairman lando zech said in a statement accompanying the gao 
study that he agrees the agency needs a firstrate investigative 
capability 
the commission will give careful consideration to the entire 
report in our continuing efforts to assure that we carry out our 
investigative responsibilities fairly and efficiently zech said 
