<TEXT>
overall black enrollment in the university of wisconsin system 
has slid 15 percent since 1980 other states are wrestling with 
similar figures in new jerseys nine state colleges and 
universities black undergraduate enrollment dropped from 18366 in 
1980 to 14237 in 1985 in rhode island 1975 blacks were enrolled 
in colleges and universities in 1986 down from 2213 in 1980 
shaw the president of the wisconsin system kicked up a storm 
last november by proposing free tuition for all minorities who 
maintained a cplus average in core academic subjects in high 
school 
the idea drew fire from many sides including minority leaders 
at the madison campus who feared it would arouse new enmity against 
blacks and other minority students some said cplus students 
didnt deserve scholarships 
in a revised design for diversity shaw has proposed 
doubling minority enrollments by 1993 in part with 1700ayear 
grants available to 500 disadvantaged wisconsin residents not 
just minorities 
shaw also wants to raise minority faculty and staff hiring by 75 
percent and to groom 15 new minority phds each year for teaching 
jobs in the system the total price tag over four years is nearly 
17 million 
shaw builds on the socalled madison plan that new university of 
wisconsin chancellor donna e shalala unveiled in february six 
weeks after arriving in madison and finding on her desk a thick 
pile of recommendations from a studentfaculty steering committee 
on minority affairs 
shalala a onetime carter administration housing official came 
to wisconsin by way of the presidency of new york citys hunter 
college where 60 percent of the 19000 students are minorities 
her blueprint fashioned after a frenetic round of meetings with 
faculty student staff and community leaders calls for doubling 
freshman minority enrollment by 1993 hiring 70 new minority 
faculty over the next three years and 125 minority staff members 
at duke university in durham nc the faculty advisory council 
reversed itself last month following faculty and student protests 
and required each of the institutions more than 50 departments to 
hire one more black faculty member by 1993 
the university of wisconsin faculty senate is being asked to 
approve an ethnic studies course requirement and shalalas 
administration endorsed construction of a multicultural center for 
students although not one left solely in the hands of minority 
students as activists had called for 
shalala found 16 million in existing funds to launch the plan 
and is asking the state legislature for 47 million more for its 
first three years some of the money will go into financial aid for 
the disadvantaged 
big debts have become a routine part of college life for many 
students in the past decade with the federal government shifting 
its emphasis from grants to loans many educators suspect that is a 
prime reason why the black share of college enrollment has dropped 
they say the military is also recruiting a growing share of black 
high school graduates with its promise of both training and a 
paycheck 
david wright 23 minority affairs director for the wisconsin 
student association says a lot of people just dont feel like 
going out and taking out 20000 in loans thats what ive had to 
do 
then theres the army be all you can be its tempting 
says wright a senior from milwaukee who is one of 11 children i 
