i dont think madison has a good image in terms of black 
students everybody who has friends who go to madison knows there 
is nothing for you to do if youre black up here theres no black 
musicthe social life is essentially null and void 
shalala says what i want to do is make this place more like 
the real world more multiethnic more multicultural there is a 
new generation of leaders not only in higher education but in 
this society we have come up through the civil rights movement 
through the peace movement and through the womens 
movementtwenty years ago i was one of those demonstraters and i 
promised myself if i ever got into a position of power i would be 
different in the way in which i led an institution 
the 47yearold shalala says madison will build its minority 
