students and older students and recruiting heavily in milwaukee 
something it has not been doing 
wisconsins population is 38 percent black 
i have to be real careful shalala says i cant be so 
hungry for minorities that we bring in kids that really cant make 
it herewere not in the remedial business 
she notes that on the same day the conference on campus racism 
was held at wingspread congress was overriding president reagans 
veto of the civil rights restoration act which bars discrimination 
in federally subsidized institutitons 
that is very important for universities she says it 
holds us accountable for every department and every program 
the success or failure of higher educations current drive to 
improve the racial climate and minority participation on campuses 
