persona id been doing a straight rock n roll show for many 
years and i got tired of it i think i outgrew it i wanted to do 
something a little more sophisticated and something i could 
entertain people of all ages with instead of just kids 
as solo performer david johansen after the 197375 new york 
dolls heyday a lot of things i would say were going over the 
audiences heads now im in a situation where i can be funny it 
is very satisfying 
every year youre singing rock you get older but the kids stay 
the same age buster is suitable entertainment for all ages people 
who like rock like buster 
he chose the obscurities from days gone by for the album 
the reason i started doing buster poindexter was i wanted to 
sing all these songs ive cataloged in my head it wasnt like 
i seriously expected to do this 
i didnt stop doing the other thing and start doing this i 
started monday nights at tramps i said i was buster poindexter so 
they wouldnt come expecting to see david johansens schtick for 
six months maybe i was singing as both it was a natural 
progression now guys on the street go yo buster 
johansen is married to portrait photographer kate simon 
he started in show business in the campy gay theater troupe 
charles ludlums ridiculous theater and moved on to become lead 
singer in a campy male rock group the new york dolls who wore 
high heels and makeup 
i guess i was a precocious kid he said in an interview 
most of the people in my family sing dance are always in plays 
i was the least inclined in that direction im the one who took it 
up as a profession now my mother comes to my shows all the time 
with her friends 
his norwegian father who died three years ago was a light 
opera singer who became an insurance salesman when he and his irish 
wife had the first of their six children we always went to see 
broadway shows when we were kids johansen said i liked them 
all 
at home on staten island david johansens street name was 
buster 
i was the one in the gang who read books he says they 
called me poindexter some people have that wanderlust both 
physically and intellectually i had a band in high school the 
blue banshees i wanted to revive that name for whatever reason 
im not sure 
after high school he worked for people who owned a store one 
of them was in the late charles ludlums theater company i just 
kind of fell into it charles ludlum was a brilliant man very 
generous with his information i learned a lot it was like an 
apprenticeship i was a lion in one play a saint in one i was an 
extra really 
then i started up the new york dolls at that time rock was 
very blue jeans and flannel shirts we wanted to bring a sense of 
flamboyance fantasy and fun to it the way we dressed scared the 
homophobes people afraid of homosexuals 
we got involved with each other because we looked like that 
i dont think we thought what we were doing was particularly 
outrageous i think it translated that way we made two albums for 
mercury released many times the best of very best of complete 
works of 
it has been said the new york dolls were the beginning of 
punk i dont agree i think it was classic rock n roll we 
played i wrote lyrics that were teen angst with a sense of humor 
johansen said the new york dolls broke up because they got tired 
of each other we were very volatile wed have an argument that 
would be it most people would say we still have this viable 
gig not us we were amateur i guess 
in retrospect it was a project that was completed i dont 
want to go around looking like that forever i see grown men still 
wearing their mothers clothes i say there but for the grace go 
i 
after the breakup johansen and another band member made money 
