<TEXT>
on a bluff with a sweeping view of the 
big sur coast 808 feet above the pacific ocean sits a restaurant 
that serves something more with its burgers than a side of fries 
nepenthe has been a popular eatery on highway 1 since the late 
1940s not just with the 15 million motorists who pass by 
annually but with many of the writers artists and thinkers who 
have given big sur its unique reputation as the birthplace of the 
human potential movement 
the restaurant designed by rowan maiden a frank lloyd wright 
disciple makes the most of its view with a dining room surrounded 
by picture windows and a wraparound bilevel patio inside and 
out there are giant fireplaces to ward off the chill of the 
notorious coastal fog 
the food ranging from quiche and burgers to steaks and red 
snapper is good and not unreasonably priced by big sur standards 
but its the history and people of nepenthe that really makes the 
place special 
the restaurant named for a mythical egyptian drug that induced 
forgetfulness and eased sorrow sits beside a log cabin built by 
the equestrian trails club in 1925 
the cabin was purchased by orson welles in the 1940s reportedly 
as a gift for rita hayworth but she never lived there and the 
property was sold again to bill and lolly fassett in 1947 
today nepenthe is managed by their grandson kirk fassett 
granddaughter erin fassett supervises the dining room and lives in 
the rustic cabin 
born and raised in big sur during the 1960s they had a good 
view of social changes here and of the changes in people who gave 
up the straight life somewhere else to seek an alternative 
lifestyle on the california coast 
in big sur there is really only one industry the 
entertainment industry restaurants and inns notes erin so 
people who wanted to live here unless they were independently 
wealthy or selfemployed ended up working in restaurants 
i know people who have phds or were doctors and didnt want 
to be doctors anymore people who dropped out of a different life 
and were working here and thats still true these people have 
gone through a real rebirth in a way a rejuvenation they get 
excited about life again she said 
every night somebody comes through and says i came here 10 
years ago and i was never able to forget it its really kind of a 
haunting community you dont forget it very easily 
</TEXT>
