conner prairie one of the nations 
most authentic 19thcentury villages is adding something new a 
stateoftheart 105 million museum center 
the museum center will open may 7 with a twoday celebration 
conner prairie six miles north of indianapolis depicts the 
lives times attitudes and values of indianas first settlers it 
stretches over 250 acres and attracts 200000 visitors annually 
youre in your own historical novel or personal john wayne 
movie said frank werner who supervises the museums 
documentation people who know nothing of the 1830s come out here 
and suddenly find themselves wrapped up in the history we awaken 
people to the realities good and bad 
the museum center will house a permanent gallery temporary 
exhibition hall audiovisual program restaurant 100seat 
theater library classrooms and administrative offices 
the center has been designed as a complement to the village 
museum smokeswoman brenda myers says its a modern visitors 
center meant to augment whats outside the village is real so why 
imitate 
open since 1974 conner prairie features citizens 
interpreting everyday events from a 19thcentury perspective 
visitors are encouraged to participate in handson activities as 
they circulate among the towns 30 authentic buildings 
kids can poke around and play here and that doesnt happen at 
most historic sites myers said there are so many generic 
living history museums and no touch places out there thats what 
we want to avoid 
we encourage active participation because we want visitors to 
get not only a sense of how people lived but how they felt how 
better to learn history 
werner said family members of all ages enjoy chatting with the 
more than 100 history interpreters at conner prairie and joining 
them in weaving making soap cooking working with wood and 
playing pioneer games 
you cant describe what the interpreters do as acting said 
