<TEXT>
soho the bohemian neighborhood famed for its 
smorgasbord of restaurants and expensive touristoriented topless 
bars is cleaning up its naughty image 
families are moving back to the once seedy halfmile square area 
of central london that was originally settled by immigrants and 
refugees 
trendy restaurants wine bars and media companies are moving 
next door to generationsold firms of tailors silversmiths and 
clockmakers reclaiming the classic georgian buildings from what 
was collectively known as the vice 
part of soho has become the capitals chinatown with gerard 
street converted into a busy mall lined with chinese restaurants 
supermarkets bookstores and pay phones with pagodastyle roofs 
the impetus for change came from sohos residents who were tired 
of gazing out their windows at pulsating pink neon signs boasting 
girls girls girls and of having to slink past peep shows 
pornographic cinemas lingerie shops and topless bars every time 
they took their children to school or shopped for groceries 
the local community realized that it was them or us 
explained bryan burrough chairman of the soho society and we 
wanted to make sure it was us 
soho became synonymous with sleaze during world war ii when 
american soldiers swarmed to its clubs and pubs but burrough said 
soho didnt hit rock bottom until the mid1970s 
prior to the mid1960s the vice was represented in the main 
by prostitutes who were fairly unnoticeable he said 
in the 1970s it became sex cinemas topless encounter bars 
all sorts of things totally outside the provisions of the law so 
ordinary legitimate businesses were being pushed out 
the 1000member soho society was founded in 1972 as a community 
group and one of first accomplishments was to have soho declared a 
conservation area meaning nothing can be demolished without 
permission from the westminster borough council 
westminster then passed tougher laws to regulate the flesh 
trade the borough set aside just 10 licenses for sex shops and a 
spokeswoman says only five were actually issued all to book and 
video stores 
burrough said about 20 more sex shops still operate illegally 
compared with a decade ago when 185 soho buildings were devoted to 
the sex industry he said 18 such buildings were on greek street 
alone but now its four short blocks are home to 18 restaurants 
three pubs two sandwich bars a patisserie and only one sex shop 
soho in the heart of londons west end theater district is 
bounded by oxford street regent street charing cross road and 
leicester square 
the name is thought to come from the ancient harehunting cry 
soho the areas cosmopolitan flavor dates back to its first 
immigrants french protestants known as huguenots who arrived in 
the late 1600s germans and italians many of them cooks and 
waiters arrived in the 1860s and 1870s followed by polish and 
russian jews many of them tailors in the 1890s 
joining the melting pot were families from almost every other 
european country as well as british colonies past and present 
indians and hong kong chinese 
in the 1960s a favorite soho haunt was carnaby street with its 
swinging fashion shops stocked with bellbottoms gogo boots 
miniskirts and fishnet stockings 
today sohos nooks and crannies are still packed with old 
established family businesses here the savile row tailors have 
their workshops and gold lace is handmade for buckingham palaces 
livery 
sprinkled among them are dozens of new film production and 
distribution offices film laboratories advertising agencies and 
other support services for londons tv and cinema industry 
street for street soho is said to have more restaurants than 
any other part of london ranging from japanese sushi bars to a 
1950sstyle chrome and formica diner 
gourmets and gourmands can wallow in a cheese shop offering 200 
varieties including cartiresized wheels of swiss emmenthal a 
coffee shop sells 25 types of fresh aromatic beans and barbecued 
ducks hang in chinese markets 
