<TEXT>
a proposal by two of the nations biggest cable 
television concerns to pay about 155 billion for the cable 
systems of the former storer communications follows a bigger 
consortiums abortive proposal to buy the properties at a higher 
price 
comcast corp and telecommunications inc announced sunday they 
had a definitive agreement to acquire sci holdings the company 
formed when storer was taken private by the investment firm 
kohlberg kravis amp roberts in a 25 billion leveraged buyout in 
1985 
sci last year sold its six television stations for about 14 
billion leaving it with cable television systems serving about 
148 million subscribers in 12 states in the east and south 
the acquisition is subject to regulatory approval and other 
conditions 
comcast and telecommunications both members of the consortium 
that proposed and later dropped a plan to acquire sci for about 
29 billion earlier this year 
