basic provisions of the bill would overhaul the system under 
which the united states imposes import curbs in retaliation for 
international trade violations and other unfair practices 
among other things it would make retaliation mandatory for 
violations except in certain cases such as national security 
it also would transfer from the president to the us trade 
representative the authority to determine whether retaliation was 
in order and if so what kind of sanctions to impose 
other central features would streamline the machinery under 
which the united states imposes import quotas and tariffs to aid 
american industries that are threatened by surges in foreign 
competition 
the measure contains scores of other features ranging from 
billions of dollars in agricultural subsidies to repeal of the 
windfall profits tax on earnings of oil companies 
